The Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy is a 16-week program designed to accelerate your path to becoming a cybersecurity specialist. With no prior knowledge required, you will gain a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration.

The bootcamp covers various topics including cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. You will also learn data loss prevention (DLP) strategies and how to navigate compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST.

Classes are conducted three times a week in a live online format, with a maximum class size of 16 students. Upon completion of the program, you will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions.

To learn more about the Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy, visit their website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop